# Buckbot Module Framework - Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` or set these variables in your deployment environment.
Required variables are marked with [REQUIRED].

## Module Framework

# [REQUIRED] Enable module loading on startup
ENABLE_MODULE_LOADING=1

# [OPTIONAL] Base URL for module cron job invocations
# Default: http://localhost:5000
MODULE_CRON_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

## Celery & Redis

# [REQUIRED] Redis broker for Celery task queue
CELERY_BROKER_URL=redis://redis.svc.tools.eqiad1.wikimedia.cloud:6379/9

# [REQUIRED] Redis result backend for Celery task results
CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND=redis://redis.svc.tools.eqiad1.wikimedia.cloud:6379/9

## Database

# Framework uses environment-based DB configuration
# Set via Toolforge secrets or .env file
# Database name auto-discovered from TOOL_DATA_DIR

## Pywikibot

# [REQUIRED] Toolforge data directory (auto-discovered)
TOOL_DATA_DIR=/data/project/buckbot

# [REQUIRED] Enable production mode (prevents accidents)
NOTDEV=1

## Authentication & Authorization

# [REQUIRED] Bot admin accounts (comma-separated usernames)
BOT_ADMIN_ACCOUNTS=chuckthebuck

# [REQUIRED] Flask session secret
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here

## Logging

# [OPTIONAL] Log level for Python logging
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# [OPTIONAL] Disable status updates in tests
# LIVE_TEST_DISABLE_STATUS_UPDATES=1

## Development (NOT for production)

# Uncomment these to enable development features
# DEBUG=1
# FLASK_ENV=development
